{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VjXR3q3DYstqyMruYvpDut","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Project Versioning Design\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4→**Status:** Design\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→After a self-reflection cycle mutates a workflow or prompt file, there is no record of\n     9→how many times the project has been evolved. This makes it hard to correlate behavior\n    10→changes with specific evolution events.\n    11→\n    12→## Design\n    13→\n    14→### Version file\n    15→\n    16→A plain integer stored in `.cloche/version`. The file is created with value `1` on\n    17→`cloche init`. The daemon increments it whenever the evolution pipeline produces at\n    18→least one change.\n    19→\n    20→```\n    21→.cloche/version\n    22→```\n    23→\n    24→Content is a single decimal integer followed by a newline, e.g. `3\\n`.\n    25→\n    26→### Increment rule\n    27→\n    28→In `internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`, after Stage 5 (Audit), check:\n    29→\n    30→```go\n    31→if len(result.Changes) > 0 {\n    32→    incrementProjectVersion(o.cfg.ProjectDir)\n    33→}\n    34→```\n    35→\n    36→`incrementProjectVersion` reads `.cloche/version`, parses the integer, increments it,\n    37→and writes it back atomically (write to a temp file, rename). If the file does not\n    38→exist, it writes `2` (treating the missing file as implicit version 1).\n    39→\n    40→### Read path\n    41→\n    42→`config.Load` gains a companion function:\n    43→\n    44→```go\n    45→func LoadVersion(projectDir string) (int, error)\n    46→```\n    47→\n    48→Returns the integer from `.cloche/version`, defaulting to `1` if the file does not\n    49→exist.\n    50→\n    51→### Surface\n    52→\n    53→- The project detail page (see project-pages design) reads the version via\n    54→  `/api/projects/{name}/info` and displays it as `v3`.\n    55→- The evolution audit log entry already records `ChangesJSON`; the version is not\n    56→  duplicated there.\n    57→\n    58→### .gitignore\n    59→\n    60→`.cloche/version` is **not** gitignored — it should be committed alongside workflow\n    61→changes so the version is visible in git history.\n    62→\n    63→`cloche init` adds `.cloche/version` to the files it creates (with content `1\\n`) but\n    64→does not add it to `.gitignore`.\n    65→\n    66→## Changes required\n    67→\n    68→| File | Change |\n    69→|------|--------|\n    70→| `internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` | Call `incrementProjectVersion` when `len(result.Changes) > 0` |\n    71→| `internal/config/config.go` | Add `LoadVersion(projectDir string) (int, error)` and `incrementProjectVersion` (unexported helper used by evolution) |\n    72→| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Write `.cloche/version` with content `1\\n` on init |\n    73→| `internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | Include version in `/api/projects/{name}/info` response |\n    74→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abc7be75-0801-4859-9ba7-1cf2d12a7505","uuid":"837252e9-7b04-4fb3-9985-9559018d068b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md","content":"# Project Versioning Design\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\n**Status:** Design\n\n## Problem\n\nAfter a self-reflection cycle mutates a workflow or prompt file, there is no record of\nhow many times the project has been evolved. This makes it hard to correlate behavior\nchanges with specific evolution events.\n\n## Design\n\n### Version file\n\nA plain integer stored in `.cloche/version`. The file is created with value `1` on\n`cloche init`. The daemon increments it whenever the evolution pipeline produces at\nleast one change.\n\n```\n.cloche/version\n```\n\nContent is a single decimal integer followed by a newline, e.g. `3\\n`.\n\n### Increment rule\n\nIn `internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`, after Stage 5 (Audit), check:\n\n```go\nif len(result.Changes) > 0 {\n    incrementProjectVersion(o.cfg.ProjectDir)\n}\n```\n\n`incrementProjectVersion` reads `.cloche/version`, parses the integer, increments it,\nand writes it back atomically (write to a temp file, rename). If the file does not\nexist, it writes `2` (treating the missing file as implicit version 1).\n\n### Read path\n\n`config.Load` gains a companion function:\n\n```go\nfunc LoadVersion(projectDir string) (int, error)\n```\n\nReturns the integer from `.cloche/version`, defaulting to `1` if the file does not\nexist.\n\n### Surface\n\n- The project detail page (see project-pages design) reads the version via\n  `/api/projects/{name}/info` and displays it as `v3`.\n- The evolution audit log entry already records `ChangesJSON`; the version is not\n  duplicated there.\n\n### .gitignore\n\n`.cloche/version` is **not** gitignored — it should be committed alongside workflow\nchanges so the version is visible in git history.\n\n`cloche init` adds `.cloche/version` to the files it creates (with content `1\\n`) but\ndoes not add it to `.gitignore`.\n\n## Changes required\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` | Call `incrementProjectVersion` when `len(result.Changes) > 0` |\n| `internal/config/config.go` | Add `LoadVersion(projectDir string) (int, error)` and `incrementProjectVersion` (unexported helper used by evolution) |\n| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Write `.cloche/version` with content `1\\n` on init |\n| `internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | Include version in `/api/projects/{name}/info` response |\n","numLines":74,"startLine":1,"totalLines":74}}}
